# AI doc router

Use this rule as the routing layer. **Canonical project facts** live in the repository (README, `docs/`, `design/`, architecture notes).

## 1) Context7 usage

Use Context7 for **external** library and platform APIs when the answer depends on current vendor documentation (frameworks, off-the-shelf engines used as libraries, build tools, browser APIs, etc.).

For in-repo behavior and architecture, read local docs and code first.

## 2) Canonical ownership (project-defined)

Maintain a short mental map; typical anchors:

| Topic | Typical canonical source (create if missing) |
|---|---|
| Tech stack and build | `README.md`, `package.json`, vendor docs as needed |
| Architecture | `docs/architecture.md` or `docs/` |
| Design intent | `design/` or GDD fragments |
| Contribution / review | `CONTRIBUTING.md` |
| AI / agent rules | `.cursor/rules/**`, `.cursor/docs/studio/**` |

If the repo has a single “index” doc (e.g. `llms.txt` or `AGENTS.md`), treat **that file** as the ownership table for **this** project and keep it updated when behavior changes.

## 2b) Common commands

| Purpose | Path |
|---|---|
| Major-change planning | `.cursor/commands/plan-major-change.md` |
| Architecture heuristic pass | `.cursor/commands/check-architecture.md` |
| Playtest procedure | `.cursor/commands/playtest.md` |
| Subagent playbooks | `.cursor/commands/subagent-playbooks.md` |

## 3) Rule routing

**Always-on:**

- `.cursor/rules/typescript-typing.mdc`
- `.cursor/rules/ai-playtesting.mdc`
- `.cursor/rules/llm.mdc`
- `.cursor/rules/migration-and-terminology.mdc`
- `.cursor/rules/subagent-and-skill-routing.mdc`
- `.cursor/rules/self-maintenance-and-drift-control.mdc`

**Scoped:**

- `.cursor/rules/runtime-discipline.mdc` for application runtime, rendering, and concurrency

Add project-specific rules under `.cursor/rules/` when a stack or pipeline needs always-on guidance.

## 4) Documentation sync gate

If behavior or public contracts change:

1. Update the project’s canonical doc(s) first.
2. Update derived rules, commands, or agent notes that restate those contracts.
3. Remove stale names and dead paths — no parallel “old vs new” guidance.

## 5) Definition of done (changes)

- Code matches the documented contract.
- Canonical docs and touched `.cursor` guidance stay consistent.
- Typecheck / tests as defined by the project pass.
